#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:5
msgid "Guidance for Discussion Moderators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:7
msgid "Discussion forums are hugely important tools in running a successful MOOC; they allow for substantive community development, in addition to being excellent sources of feedback and ideas for future iterations of the course."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:11
msgid "Moderators are the key to effectively managing these online communities. Moderators keep the discussions productive and relay important information (errors, learner confusion with or interest in particular topics, and so on) to the rest of the course team. Discussions can be moderated by any of a number of members of the course team, but dedicating enough time to moderation is the best way to cultivate a successful discussion culture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:18
msgid "Feel free to use some or all of the information in this section to guide the contributions of your discussion moderators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:27
msgid "Responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:29
msgid "Answer basic questions posed by learners, and direct learners with questions to the right resources: syllabi, course documents, course updates, useful lecture segments, example problems, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:33
msgid "Relay reports of errata, common misconceptions and questions, highly disruptive participants, bugs, and amusing or interesting posts to the most appropriate course team members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:37
msgid "Enforce the Honor Code by editing or deleting problem answers, or requests for answers, promptly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:40
msgid "Edit out offensive content from the discussion, and remind the originators of discussion etiquette and expectations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:43
msgid "Communicate problems and successes to your fellow moderators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:45
msgid "Identify learners whose presence in the discussions has a strongly positive impact. These learners can be promoted to community TA role and publicly acknowledged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:49
msgid "Add helpful items to the FAQ or to a welcome message or course handout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:53
msgid "Qualities of Good Discussion Moderators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:55
msgid "Good or great content knowledge: stellar learners from previous years often make good moderators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:58
msgid "Solid communication skills: the ability to organize positive, consistent, and effective communication with learners, other moderators, and members of the course team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:62
msgid "Time: keeping up-to-date with the discussions for a large MOOC requires at least 5 hours per week for reading posts, replying to or editing posts, and communicating with the other moderators and the course team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:66
msgid "Enthusiasm: this is the best predictor of moderator excellence!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:70
msgid "Best Practices for Discussion Moderation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:72
msgid "Always maintain a positive attitude. Keeping a positive attitude is crucial to encouraging participation in the discussion community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:75
msgid "Encourage discussion between learners. Actively thank learners who answer the questions of others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:78
msgid "Use the course's FAQ and updates or handouts on **Course** pages as resources. Provide links to these pages in your responses when appropriate. Suggest that information be added to these resources when necessary to respond to a common question or fix confusion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:83
msgid "Always make it obvious that you have read the learner's question. When you post a response, make sure that you are on topic. Respond in the context of the thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:87
msgid "Develop a discussion persona. Try to answer your questions in your own slightly unique way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:92
msgid "Guidelines for Specific Types of Posts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:94
msgid "Certain types of posts require more attention from the moderators than others, or might need to be handled in a particular way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:99
msgid "Time Sensitive Problems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:101
msgid "Try to be present on discussion threads when assignment due dates are approaching or new content is being released. The discussions tend to be extra busy at these times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:105
msgid "Alert the course team about problems that need to be dealt with quickly, such as problems with graded assignments. Setting up a course email address that is checked frequently is a good way to manage such alerts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:111
msgid "Content Questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:113
msgid "Assist with content questions sensitively, but be careful not to post spoilers. Do not ask learners to post their solutions!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:116
msgid "A good guiding question can be better than an answer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:120
msgid "Redundant Posts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:122
msgid "When possible, help discourage redundancy by responding to such posts with links to an earlier or higher quality thread that asks the same question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:125
msgid "When responding to a post, search for similar posts and respond to the most pertinent thread. Redirect the other posts to the thread with your response and then close the redundant threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:131
msgid "Off Topic, Inappropriate, or Offensive Posts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:133
msgid "Do not simply delete inappropriate or offensive posts. Instead, edit and explain why the posts were edited. Inappropriate posts include spoilers, solutions, and information on how to pirate educational materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:137
msgid "Check links that learners post. If you find links to offensive sites and materials, they need to be edited quickly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:142
msgid "Bugs or Errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:144
msgid "Check to confirm that there is in fact an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:146
msgid "If not, suggest to the learners that they check their work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:148
msgid "If so, contact members of the course team, and notify the thread that the error has been reported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:151
msgid "Use language that does not assign blame or discourage users from the platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:154
msgid "You might say: “Thanks for letting us know about that issue. We are working with edX to get it fixed as quickly as possible.”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:159
msgid "Feature Requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:161
msgid "Keep an organized collection of feature requests cultivated by the course team. That list can subsequently be shared with an edX product manager, who will log those requests internally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:165
msgid "Reply to the post to let the person know that their request was heard, without promising that the feature will be implemented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:168
msgid "You might say: \"Thanks for your suggestion. I've logged it for review by edX staff, who will prioritize feature requests on the development roadmap.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../shared/manage_discussions/discussion_guidance_moderators.rst:171
msgid "Search the discussions for other similar requests, and respond to and close those as well."
msgstr ""

